{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857507369,"sessionID":"ses_286a50ac4ffe4tDrzPYhHoDy9z","part":{"id":"prt_d795b17590017aNNla8qAhze4Q","messageID":"msg_d795b08a0001j8cSOYwEWNukti","sessionID":"ses_286a50ac4ffe4tDrzPYhHoDy9z","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a3a0d457686541c9bb0206fd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the PicoD JWT middleware in `pkg/picod`.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-017\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/picod`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: S\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)-protected APIs. This delta covers the JWT middleware implementation in `pkg/picod`, specifically the AuthManager component that handles RSA public key loading and JWT token validation.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Requirements\n23: \n24: ### AR-017-001: RSA Public Key Loading\n25: \n26: **Description:** The system must support loading an RSA public key from an environment variable for JWT signature verification.\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: AR-017-001-A — Load valid RSA public key from environment variable\n29: \n30: **GIVEN** the environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is set with a valid PEM-encoded RSA public key  \n31: **WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` is called  \n32: **THEN** the public key is successfully parsed and stored in the AuthManager  \n33: **AND** subsequent calls to `GetPublicKey()` return the loaded RSA public key\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: AR-017-001-B — Missing environment variable\n38: \n39: **GIVEN** the environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is not set  \n40: **WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` is called  \n41: **THEN** an error is returned with message `\"environment variable PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY is not set\"`\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: AR-017-001-C — Invalid PEM format\n46: \n47: **GIVEN** the environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is set with invalid PEM data  \n48: **WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` is called  \n49: **THEN** an error is returned with message `\"failed to decode PEM block\"`\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: AR-017-001-D — Non-RSA public key\n54: \n55: **GIVEN** the environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is set with a valid PEM-encoded EC (elliptic curve) public key  \n56: **WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` is called  \n57: **THEN** an error is returned with message `\"public key is not an RSA key\"`\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: AR-017-001-E — Thread-safe key update\n62: \n63: **GIVEN** an AuthManager has already loaded a valid public key  \n64: **WHEN** multiple goroutines call `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` concurrently to update the key  \n65: **THEN** no race conditions occur  \n66: **AND** `GetPublicKey()` always returns a valid public key or nil\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ### AR-017-002: JWT Bearer Token Validation\n71: \n72: **Description:** The middleware must validate JWT Bearer tokens from the Authorization header using the loaded RSA public key.\n73: \n74: #### Scenario: AR-017-002-A — Missing Authorization header\n75: \n76: **GIVEN** an HTTP request is made to a protected endpoint without an `Authorization` header  \n77: **WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n78: **THEN** the request is rejected with HTTP status 401  \n79: **AND** the response body contains `{\"error\": \"Missing authorization header\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"JWT required: Use Bearer <token>\"}`\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: AR-017-002-B — Invalid Authorization header format (not Bearer)\n84: \n85: **GIVEN** an HTTP request is made with `Authorization: Basic dXNlcjpwYXNz`  \n86: **WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n87: **THEN** the request is rejected with HTTP status 401  \n88: **AND** the response body contains `{\"error\": \"Invalid authorization header format\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"Use Bearer <token>\"}`\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: AR-017-002-C — Malformed Bearer token format\n93: \n94: **GIVEN** an HTTP request is made with `Authorization: Bearer` (no token)  \n95: **WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n96: **THEN** the request is rejected with HTTP status 401  \n97: **AND** the response body contains `{\"error\": \"Invalid authorization header format\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"Use Bearer <token>\"}`\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: AR-017-002-D — Public key not configured\n102: \n103: **GIVEN** an HTTP request is made with a valid Bearer token but the AuthManager has no public key loaded (publicKey is nil)  \n104: **WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n105: **THEN** the request is rejected with HTTP status 401  \n106: **AND** the response body contains `{\"error\": \"Invalid token\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"Public key not configured\"}`\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: #### Scenario: AR-017-002-E — Valid JWT token with RSA signature\n111: \n112: **GIVEN** an HTTP request is made with a valid JWT token signed with the corresponding RSA private key  \n113: **WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n114: **THEN** the request is allowed to proceed to the next handler  \n115: **AND** `c.Next()` is called\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: AR-017-002-F — Invalid JWT signature\n120: \n121: **GIVEN** an HTTP request is made with a JWT token that has an invalid RSA signature  \n122: **WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n123: **THEN** the request is rejected with HTTP status 401  \n124: **AND** the response body contains `{\"error\": \"Invalid token\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"verification failed\"}`\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: AR-017-002-G — JWT with wrong signing method\n129: \n130: **GIVEN** an HTTP request is made with a JWT token signed using HS256 (HMAC) instead of RS256 (RSA)  \n131: **WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n132: **THEN** the request is rejected with HTTP status 401  \n133: **AND** the response body contains detail about the unexpected signing method\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: AR-017-002-H — Expired JWT token\n138: \n139: **GIVEN** an HTTP request is made with a JWT token that has expired (exp claim is in the past)  \n140: **WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n141: **THEN** the request is rejected with HTTP status 401  \n142: **AND** the response indicates the token is invalid due to expiration\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: AR-017-002-I — JWT token without expiration claim\n147: \n148: **GIVEN** an HTTP request is made with a JWT token that has no `exp` (expiration) claim  \n149: **WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n150: **THEN** the request is rejected with HTTP status 401  \n151: **AND** the response indicates expiration is required\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: AR-017-002-J — Request body size limit enforcement\n156: \n157: **GIVEN** a valid JWT token is provided in the Authorization header  \n158: **WHEN** `AuthMiddleware()` processes the request  \n159: **THEN** the request body is wrapped with `http.MaxBytesReader` limiting it to 32 MiB  \n160: **AND** oversized requests will be rejected before reaching handlers\n161: \n162: ---\n163: \n164: ### AR-017-003: Public Key Accessor\n165: \n166: **Description:** The system must provide thread-safe access to the loaded public key.\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: AR-017-003-A — Get public key after loading\n169: \n170: **GIVEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` has successfully loaded a valid RSA public key  \n171: **WHEN** `GetPublicKey()` is called  \n172: **THEN** the RSA public key is returned  \n173: **AND** the operation is thread-safe (read lock)\n174: \n175: ---\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: AR-017-003-B — Get public key when not loaded\n178: \n179: **GIVEN** the AuthManager was created with `NewAuthManager()` (no key loaded)  \n180: **WHEN** `GetPublicKey()` is called  \n181: **THEN** nil is returned  \n182: **AND** no error occurs\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ### AR-017-004: RequireAuth Helper\n187: \n188: **Description:** The system should provide a convenience middleware that loads the public key on first use and then validates tokens.\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: AR-017-004-A — RequireAuth loads key and validates\n191: \n192: **GIVEN** the environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is set with a valid RSA public key  \n193: **WHEN** `RequireAuth()` middleware is invoked on a request with a valid JWT  \n194: **THEN** the public key is loaded from environment  \n195: **AND** the request proceeds through `AuthMiddleware()`\n196: \n197: ---\n198: \n199: #### Scenario: AR-017-004-B — RequireAuth fails if key cannot be loaded\n200: \n201: **GIVEN** the environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is not set  \n202: **WHEN** `RequireAuth()` middleware is invoked  \n203: **THEN** the server logs a fatal error via `klog.Fatalf`\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ## Architecture Notes\n208: \n209: ### Data Structures\n210: \n211: ```go\n212: type AuthManager struct {\n213:     publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n214:     mutex     sync.RWMutex\n215: }\n216: ```\n217: \n218: ### Constants\n219: \n220: | Constant | Value | Description |\n221: |----------|-------|-------------|\n222: | `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | Environment variable for RSA public key |\n223: | `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` (32 MiB) | Maximum request body size |\n224: \n225: ### Key Behaviors\n226: \n227: 1. **Public Key Loading**: RSA public key loaded from PEM-encoded environment variable\n228: 2. **Token Validation**: JWT Bearer tokens validated using RSA signature\n229: 3. **Thread Safety**: RWMutex protects public key access for concurrent reads\n230: 4. **Validation Rules**:\n231:    - Signing method must be RSA (RS256, RS384, RS512)\n232:    - Expiration (`exp`) claim is required\n233:    - Issued at (`iat`) claim is validated\n234:    - 1 minute leeway allowed for time tolerance\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ## References\n239: \n240: - Module: `pkg/picod`\n241: - Auth Implementation: `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n242: - Related: AR-015 (PicoD Command Execution API - includes full server integration)\n\n(End of file - total 242 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the PicoD JWT middleware in `pkg/picod`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-017\n- **Module**: `pkg/picod`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nPicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)-protected APIs. This delta covers the JWT middleware implementation in `pkg/picod`, specifically the AuthManager component that handles RSA public key loading and JWT token validation.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775857507335,"end":1775857507366}}}}
